author: Amanda Lynne
title: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce Red Carpet Debut Expected at Met Gala
text:
Taylor Swift and her
boyfriend, Travis Kelce, haven’t been trying to hide their relationship. The singer and the Kansas City Chiefs football player have been seen in public on several occasions. The duo have taken their love and showed off some PDA at many different locations. Whether they’re on the football field, celebrating with friends, having dinner, or enjoying a romantic vacation. Swift and Kelce have no problem showing their love for one another. They were most recently spotted dancing and laughing at Coachella. However, they may be ready to make their official red carpet debut at the upcoming Met Gala.
According to
The Sun, Swift and Kelce are on the guest list for the 2024 Meta Gala. The social event is a who’s who of fashion and fame. Over the years, several A-list celebrities have been invited to the ball. This year, the singer and the athlete would certainly steal the show if they were to attend.
Will Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce Attend the Met Gala?
The event is set to take place on May 6, just three days before Taylor Swift is scheduled to head back on tour. Meanwhile,
Travis Kelce’s schedule is open until July, when he’s required to head back to the NFL for training camp. Of course, fans are dying to know if the couple will be appearing at the event, and are hoping to see them dressed to the nines on the red carpet.
“Taylor and Travis at Coachella??? We are so close to seeing them in Met Gala OMG,” one fan wrote via Twitter. “I have absolutely convinced myself that Taylor and Travis are going to the Met Gala together and I refuse to be wrong about it,” another comment read.
Meanwhile,
Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce have been enjoying their downtime together. It seems that they’re trying to spend as much quality time together as possible before their careers pull them apart again. Because of this, they may opt to skip the Met Gala in favor of alone time. However, fans are hopeful that they’ll attend and completely steal the spotlight.
